<ol class="d-block">
	<li>Go to this <a href="https://www.facebook.com/dyi/?referrer=ayi" target="_blank">link</a><br/></li>

	<li>Change the Format to JSON <img class="d-block" src="fb_download_instruction/step1.png" alt="how to change data format" width="800"/><br/></li>
	<li>Change the data range to "All Time" (or any period you want)<img class="d-block" src="fb_download_instruction/step2.png" width="800" alt="how to change data range"/><br/></li>
	<li>
		Select the type of information you want to download.<br/>
		Note that Privasight cannot process zip files that is larger than 512 MB. Zip file is usually smaller than this size excluding "Messages" & "Posts" with low media quality.
		<img class="d-block" src="fb_download_instruction/step3.png" width="800" alt="selecting what data to download"/>
		<br/>
		Here is the list of information supported by Privasight (the list will keep expanding)
		<ul>
			<li>
				Your Topics <img class="d-block" src="fb_download_instruction/your-topics.png" width="800" alt="your topics location on the download page"/>
			</li>
			<li>
				Ads information <img class="d-block" src="fb_download_instruction/ads-info.png" width="800" alt="ads information location on the download page"/>
			</li>
		</ul>
		<br/>
	</li>
	<li>Press the "Request a download" Button<img class="d-block" src="fb_download_instruction/step4.png" width="800" alt="location of the request a download button"/><br/></li>
	<li>Switch to the "Available files" tab and press the "Download" button on the first row.<br/>
		(It will takes a while for Facebook to generate the Facebook Information file. You will usually receive an email notification from them when the file is ready)<img class="d-block" src="fb_download_instruction/step5.png" width="800" alt="location of the request a download button"/><br/></li>
	<li>Response to the prompts and you should see a zip file being downloaded to your download folder. This is the file you have to upload to Privasight.<img class="d-block" src="fb_download_instruction/step6.png" alt="zip file being downloaded" width="800"/><br/></li>
</ol>

